    TGTurnByTurnSupportFragment

    public abstract class TGBaseTurnByTurnSupportFragment
extends TGBaseSupportMapFragment
implements TGBaseTurnByTurnContract.View
    An implementation of TGBaseSupportMapFragment that allows for easy interaction with the TGNavigationService navigation. This Fragment can be used in conjunction with TGSupportMapFragment to create a fully functional navigation and search application. Be careful when passing in a route id, this fragment will evict the route from the route cache.

      • startNavigation

        protected void startNavigation()
                        throws java.lang.IllegalStateException
        Here we start the route guidance. We update the destination and make a call to the TGNavigationService to start. You must define a ServiceConnection like the one at the bottom of this class (navServiceConn)
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the map or route is unavailable

      • onNavigationCanceled

        protected abstract void onNavigationCanceled()
        This is called as soon as the navigation has been canceled. It is identical to observing the navigation state changing to TGNavigationState.CANCELED At this point navigation should be restarted or the fragment closed.
